TYPE: Test,
TARGET: control (ambient sensor) module internal circuit around light sensor and comparator/driver,
DESCRIPTION: With the module opened, probe the voltage at the comparator/driver output that commands the relay coil, while sweeping ambient light and the sensitivity potentiometer. Also measure the supply voltage to this circuit (between its V+ rail and ground). Determine whether the comparator output ever toggles between near‑0 V and near‑supply, and verify that the logic supply is present and stable.,
RESULT: The comparator/driver output commanding the relay coil does not toggle between near-0 V and near-supply; it remains at approximately 11.99 V on the positive side and 0.36 V on the negative side. The circuit’s logic supply is present and stable at about 12 V.
